717824f-a.title: Manhattan: Isham Street - Broadway
717824f-a.text:
The N.W. corner of Isham Park, Broadway, west side, opposite 214th Street.
October 26, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

717818f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - Isham Street
717818f-a.text:
Broadway, at the S.W. corner of Isham Street (right, not seen),
showing the Church of the Good Shepherd, R.C. and its Rectory, that face
on Cooper Street which parallels Broadway.
June 8, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

717819f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - Isham Street
717819f-a.text:
Broadway, at the S.W. corner of Isham Street, and showing a view west-
ward on Isham Street. Building shown is the rectory of the Church of the
DTood Shepherd and is at the S.E. corner of Cooper Street.
June 8, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
